obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4508  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rabbit Anti-PGRN antibody (Invitrogen) labels puncta colocalizing with the postsynaptic marker PSD-95 and the presynaptic marker VGLUT-1 in hippocampal primary cultures at DIV 14 indicating the presence of Progranulin at excitatory glutamatergic synapses. As GFP-tagged Progranulin is shown to be transported in axons and dendrites (Fig. 2) its presence in pre-and postsynaptic compartments can be assumed.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The anti-PGRN antibody shows a similar pattern of expression as GFP-PGRN indicating that the antibody might be specific for endogenous PGRN (also shown in S1).\nThe paper shows colocalization with both pre and postsynaptic markers: vGlut1 and PSD95 (arrowheads), however, due to insufficient resolution of the images, the term \"synapse\" was used.. Experimental description: Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18)\nSprague Dawley rats as previously described (p. 5419)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4508" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

